# Theming and shadcn UI usage

Use the app's central theme variables. Do not hardcode colors in components.

- Use brand CSS variables defined in [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css)
  - Examples: `var(--brand-primary)`, `var(--brand-primary-dark)`, `var(--brand-secondary)`, `var(--brand-accent)`, `var(--brand-foreground)`, `var(--brand-soft-mint-a)`, `var(--brand-soft-mint-ring)`
  - Where appropriate, prefer shadcn tokens (already mapped to brand vars): `var(--primary)`, `var(--accent)`, `var(--destructive)`
- Avoid hardcoded hex values in TSX. Use Tailwind + CSS variables (e.g., `text-[color:var(--brand-primary)]`).
- Prefer shadcn primitives from `@/components/ui/*` when they improve consistency (e.g., [button.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx), [input.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/input.tsx), [dialog.tsx](mdc:src/components/ui/dialog.tsx)).

